[BIO-INTEL-2026-001] — Computation: Synaptic Plasticity 2.0 (Pillar 1)

System: Computation / Synaptic Architecture / Learning

Description:
The human brain closes critical learning windows after adolescence due to DNMT3A‑mediated BDNF/Arc promoter methylation, perineuronal net (PNN) consolidation, and reduced trophic factor turnover. This developmental lock severely limits adult adaptive capacity, lifelong skill acquisition, and recovery from injury.

Core challenge: 👉 Reversing epigenetic brakes without triggering seizure synchrony, destabilizing established memory networks, or causing catastrophic interference.

Failure Mode:
Synaptic Saturation & Memory Interference.
Uncontrolled potentiation degrades long‑term memories during re‑encoding. Global BDNF elevation lowers seizure threshold.

Physical Model:
Hebbian plasticity constrained by PNNs and declining BDNF:
$\Delta w_{ij} \propto x_i x_j - \lambda(t) w_{ij}$, with $\lambda(t)$ increasing exponentially via DNMT3A and reduced Arc/PSD‑95 turnover.

Limitations:

· Epigenetic modifiers lack cell‑type & temporal specificity.
· AAV delivery triggers microglial inflammation.
· Constitutive BDNF elevation causes network instability.

Constraints:

· BBB penetration.
· AAV payload ceiling (~4.7 kb).
· Off‑target methylation risks.
· Long‑term safety monitoring.

Current Solutions:
Cognitive training, BDNF mimetics (LM22A‑4), tDCS/tACS, early CRISPR‑dCas9 tools.
→ Transient, non‑specific, poor CNS penetration.

Research Gap:
No reversible, cell‑type‑specific, temporally gated system that reopens adult plasticity while preserving memory stability and avoiding seizures.

AI Opportunity:
Closed‑loop epigenetic control + neural decoders that predict optimal plasticity windows and dynamically titrate CRISPRa dosage.

Proposed Directions (2026 Upgrade):

· Split‑CRISPRa with dual gating – Arc/Fos activity‑dependent promoter (spatial) + doxycycline control (temporal).
· NPY co‑expression – endogenous anticonvulsant to counter BDNF’s pro‑excitatory effects.
· Activity‑gated PNN remodeling – chondroitinase ABC expressed only during the same gate to avoid paradoxical deficit exacerbation.
· mRNA / saRNA delivery – transient CRISPRa expression, reversible, no integration risk.
· In vivo validation – long‑term LTP tracking + continuous EEG for subclinical seizure detection.

Impact Level: Critical – enables lifelong cognitive scaling without degradation.

