[BIO-INTEL-2026-002] — Input/Output: The Universal Sensorium (Pillar 2)

System: Input / Perception / Sensory Bandwidth

Description:
Human vision is restricted to ~400–700 nm due to opsin silencing and chromophore constraints. This narrow spectral window limits environmental data acquisition, spatial reasoning, and adaptive decision‑making compared to species with UV/NIR sensitivity.

Core challenge: 👉 Integrating novel UV/NIR photoreceptors without spectral crosstalk, phototoxicity, or cortical remapping failure.

Failure Mode:
Spectral Crosstalk & Neural Overload.
Mixed signals cause perceptual confusion. Slow opsin kinetics degrade temporal resolution. Adult visual cortex fails to segregate novel channels without targeted training.

Physical Model:
Phototransduction: $cGMP \xrightarrow{light} PDE \rightarrow \Delta[Ca^{2+}] \rightarrow$ hyperpolarization.
Opsin off‑kinetics: $\tau_{off} \propto 1/k_{decay}$; natural human opsins lack UV/NIR absorption.

Limitations:

· Slow kinetics, thermal noise, phototoxicity.
· Immune rejection of viral vectors.
· No validated adult cortical remapping protocol.

Constraints:

· Retinal cell‑type specificity (bipolar vs. ganglion).
· AAV cargo limit.
· Chromophore availability for novel opsins.
· Long‑term photoreceptor health.

Current Solutions:
Optogenetic restoration (GS030, MCO‑010 – broadband visible only), synthetic opsins (ChR2, ReaChR).
→ Monochromatic, poor temporal fidelity, no UV/NIR expansion.

Research Gap:
No validated pathway for adult cortical remapping of UV/NIR inputs alongside visible light without perceptual confusion.

AI Opportunity:
Neural decoders + spectral unmixing models + closed‑loop neurofeedback for channel segregation.

Proposed Directions (2026 Upgrade):

· Chimeric fast opsins – UV‑optimized and NIR‑optimized variants on ReaChR/ChroME scaffolds ($\tau_{off}<5$ ms).
· Cell‑type specific delivery – GRM6 (bipolar) promoter.
· Dual‑AAV or nanoparticles – bypass 4.7 kb limit.
· Mandatory cortical neurofeedback – 4–6 week VR‑based “chromatic unmixing” protocol (NIR‑to‑visible translation that gradually fades, forcing the cortex to segregate).
· Light‑gated safety switch – inducible caspase for phototoxicity rescue.

Impact Level: High – directly increases B_connection diversity and environmental modeling capacity.

