[BIO-INTEL-2026-003] — Error Correction: Radiation‑Hardened Cellular Architecture (Pillar 3)

System: Error Correction / Genomic Stability / Substrate Robustness

Description:
Ionizing radiation causes DNA double‑strand breaks (DSBs), oxidative damage, and mtDNA degradation, degrading neural function and limiting long‑duration space/medical operation.

Core challenge: 👉 Deploying tardigrade Dsup/TRID1 protection without constitutive neurotoxicity, transcriptional interference, or genomic instability.

Failure Mode:
Cumulative Genomic Degradation & Dsup Neurotoxicity.
Constitutive Dsup expression in post‑mitotic neurons causes chromatin condensation, DNA damage, and cell death – the opposite of protection.

Physical Model:
Damage: $dD/dt = \phi\sigma$; Repair: $R \propto [PARP][NAD^+] \cdot \text{PhaseSep}(TRID1)$.
But in neurons, $\text{Survival} \propto 1/[\text{Dsup}]$ at high concentrations.

Limitations:

· Constitutive Dsup interferes with transcription and is neurotoxic.
· TRID1 phase separation kinetics poorly characterized.
· Off‑target integration risks.

Constraints:

· 50+ population doubling oncogenesis screen.
· Nuclear localization signal optimisation.
· Inducible expression (avoid constitutive).
· BBB delivery.

Current Solutions:
Amifostine (systemic toxicity, short half‑life), physical shielding (heavy), PARP1 overexpression (NAD+ depletion).
→ Poor CNS penetration, no neuronal safety data.

Research Gap:
No inducible, damage‑responsive, dual‑mechanism (shield+repair) system validated for human neurons without constitutive expression.

AI Opportunity:
ML protein structure prediction for human‑tardigrade chimeras + predictive genomic stability modeling.

Proposed Directions (2026 Upgrade):

· Inducible mRNA / saRNA delivery – no integration, dose‑titratable, avoids constitutive neurotoxicity.
· ATM/ATR‑responsive promoter – Dsup/TRID1 expressed only when DNA damage is detected (“smoke detector” circuit).
· Ku70‑Dsup fusion – targets shielding to DSB sites, reducing off‑target chromatin binding.
· Mito‑targeted Dsup – protects mtDNA.
· Degron‑tagged TRID1 – phosphorylation‑sensitive degron ensures repair hub dissolves after damage clearance.
· Preclinical safety mandate – primary neuron toxicity assay + 50‑doubling oncogenesis screen.

Impact Level: Critical – required for interplanetary operation and long‑term neural preservation.

