[BIO-INTEL-2026-004] — Operating System: Maximizing Conscious Coherence (Φ) (Pillar 4)

System: Operating System / Causal Integration / Unified Experience

Description:
Intelligence requires unified causal integration (Φ). Low Φ correlates with fragmented reasoning and poor decision coherence. However, Φ is non‑computable for whole‑brain networks, and no direct epigenetic intervention has been validated.

Core challenge: 👉 Elevating measurable coherence (PCI) without inducing epileptic synchrony or metabolic overload.

Failure Mode:
Causal Fragmentation & Network Desynchronisation.
Disconnected cortical hubs produce siloed processing. High‑frequency recurrence raises seizure risk.

Physical Model:
PCI ≈ 0.31–0.62 in healthy adults; <0.25 unconscious.
Φ is intractable for $N>10$; PCI is the validated proxy.

Limitations:

· PCI requires TMS‑EEG (low throughput, poor spatial resolution).
· No known causal pathway from epigenetics to Φ.
· Metabolic cost of recurrence.

Constraints:

· Non‑invasive measurement limits.
· Individual connectome variability.
· Seizure risk during coherence elevation.

Current Solutions:
TMS‑EEG PCI, IIT 4.0 theory, tACS/tDCS, anesthesia mapping.
→ Transient, non‑specific, no durable enhancement.

Research Gap:
No validated, non‑invasive, spatially resolved Φ proxy that can be epigenetically modulated and tracked longitudinally.

AI Opportunity:
ML surrogate Φ estimators + closed‑loop neuromodulation + EWAS of high‑PCI phenotypes.

Proposed Directions (2026 Upgrade):

· Replace Φ with PCI‑ST as the primary measurable target.
· Launch EWAS – scATAC‑seq of prefrontal/insular cortex from high‑PCI vs. baseline subjects.
· Target L5 pyramidal neurons (integration hubs) using CaMKIIα‑driven CRISPRa to boost recurrent connectivity.
· Multi‑circuit approach – optimise integration across sensory, cognitive, interoceptive, executive, and limbic circuits (2025 Multi‑Circuit Theory).
· Closed‑loop PCI neurofeedback – real‑time PCI monitoring to reinforce high‑coherence states.
· Seizure safety – real‑time EEG detection algorithms in any stimulation protocol.

Impact Level: Critical – targets the super‑linear β term (β=1.35) in IISL.

