[BIO-INTEL-2026-006] — Glial‑Neuronal Lactate Shuttle Engineering (Pillar 6)

System: Support Architecture / Metabolic Coupling / Neurogenesis

Description:
Astrocyte‑neuron lactate shuttling governs activity‑dependent neurogenesis via histone lactylation (H3K18la) and the MDM2‑p53 pathway. Lactate is both fuel and epigenetic signal.

Core challenge: 👉 Enhancing MCT1/MCT2‑mediated lactate flux without intracellular acidosis, pH dysregulation, or MDM2‑p53‑mediated cell cycle arrest.

Failure Mode:
Metabolic Acidosis & Shuttle Decoupling.
Isolated MCT2 upregulation causes intracellular acidosis (lactate import faster than buffering). Isolated MCT1 upregulation causes lactate accumulation and MDM2‑p53 activation, blocking neurogenesis.

Physical Model:
$J_{lac} = k_{MCT}([Lac]_{astro} - [Lac]_{neuron})$
$H3K18la \propto [Lac]_{nuc} \cdot p300$
$\Delta pH \propto -J_{lac} / \text{BufferCapacity}$

Limitations:

· MCT1 and MCT2 must be co‑upregulated in different cell types.
· No pH buffering leads to acidosis.
· Real‑time lactate sensing lacking.

Constraints:

· pH buffering capacity maintenance.
· Dual‑promoter coordination (GFAP vs. Synapsin).
· Long‑term glial health.

Current Solutions:
Exogenous lactate, MCT modulators (AR‑C155858), exercise, ketogenic diet.
→ Systemic, transient, no epigenetic coupling.

Research Gap:
No coordinated MCT1/MCT2 enhancement with real‑time pH buffering and validated H3K18la‑driven neurogenesis.

AI Opportunity:
Genetically encoded lactate sensors (Laconic FRET) + ML‑driven metabolic pacing.

Proposed Directions (2026 Upgrade):

· Dual‑promoter AAV – GFAP‑MCT1 (astrocytes) + Synapsin‑MCT2 (neurons/NSCs).
· MCT2‑CAII fusion protein – physically tether Carbonic Anhydrase II to MCT2 to create a “proton sink” at the point of entry.
· MDM2‑p53 monitoring – p53 activity reporter; use nutlin‑3a as safety valve if hyperactivated.
· Laconic FRET sensor – real‑time lactate concentration feedback.
· CUT&Tag for H3K18la – confirm epigenetic engagement.

Impact Level: High – enables activity‑dependent structural scaling, coupling metabolism directly to plasticity.

