[BIO-INTEL-2026-008] — Chronobiological Temporal Architecture Tuning (Pillar 8)

System: Temporal Gating / Metabolic Synchronization / Plasticity Windows

Description:
Circadian CLOCK/BMAL1 cycles gate synaptic plasticity, metabolism, repair, and memory consolidation. Modern environments desynchronise these cycles, fragmenting plasticity windows and reducing cognitive scaling.

Core challenge: 👉 Sharpening circadian amplitude and extending peak‑plasticity windows without disrupting peripheral clocks or sleep architecture.

Failure Mode:
Circadian Fragmentation & Metabolic Desynchronisation.
Dampened amplitude reduces LTP induction windows. Constitutive BMAL1 upregulation disrupts peripheral clocks and sleep.

Physical Model:
Goodwin oscillator: $dX/dt = k/(1+Z^n) - \gamma X$
Amplitude $A \propto CLOCK/BMAL1 / Rev-erb\alpha$
Integrated intelligence $\propto \int B(t)C(t) dt$, which collapses as phase variance $\sigma_\phi$ increases.

Limitations:

· SCN manipulation invasive.
· Constitutive BMAL1 disrupts sleep.
· Pharmacological modulators lack tissue specificity.

Constraints:

· Peripheral clock preservation.
· REM/SWS sleep maintenance.
· Non‑invasive amplitude control.

Current Solutions:
Melatonin, light therapy, time‑restricted eating, Rev‑erbα agonists (SR9009 – clinical trials).
→ Phase‑shifting, not amplitude‑sharpening; transient.

Research Gap:
No inducible, phase‑specific circadian amplifier that extends adult plasticity windows while preserving sleep.

AI Opportunity:
Closed‑loop chronobiology + ML‑driven light/acoustic/tDCS pacing + wearable phase tracking.

Proposed Directions (2026 Upgrade):

· REV‑ERBα agonist (not BMAL1 upregulation) – sharpen amplitude by deepening the trough (e.g., SR9009).
· Phase‑specific BMAL1 stabilization – BMAL1 variant resistant to ubiquitination, expressed under Rev‑erbα‑responsive promoter.
· Closed‑loop light/CRISPRa hybrid – light‑gated CRISPRa for CLOCK/BMAL1 amplitude, activated only during subjective morning.
· Non‑invasive amplitude enhancement – dawn‑simulating light + morning blue + evening amber.
· Sleep architecture preservation – wearable EEG monitoring; if REM/SWS reduced, titrate intervention or add gaboxadol.
· SCN‑targeted delivery – retrograde AAV from retina to SCN to spare peripheral clocks.

Impact Level: High – multiplies efficacy of all other pillars by aligning them with peak biological windows.

